review_title: Just try once, your dentist won't thank you but your mouth will
reviews: Close your eyes, open your mouth, apply paste and go to town with this fine-bristled tooth cleaner! Why am I bothering to review this seemingly overpriced product? Well, I have pericoronitis on lower left wisdom tooth and nightly irrigation ritual had me seriously considering dental surgery. Plus I have no patience for flossing, I mostly end up hurting my gums. And even the ultra-softs could not reach those pesky corner chompers. So I bought this on a whim and tested it the minuted it arrived. Results-- bristles are fine, firm but very soft. Takes care of interdenal food debris which means nightly flossing is not necessary. The narrow head provides easy access to tight corners and my molars have never been cleaner. BUT this brush WILL NOT magically whiten your teeth (c'mon be realistic!)ADVICE-- Try once. If your teeth are still not squeaky clean, I dunno, throw a hisssy fit or something. You probably need an electric brush anyway. Just saying..

review_title: Love these! Softest toothbrushes I've ever used!
reviews: I like to try different kind of brushes. I have tried almost all good brushes available in the market and this is the brush which I like the most. In this review, I will share good and bad things about this brush based on my personal experience. So here we go:----------------------📦 Box Contents:----------------------3x Colgate Slim Soft Charcoal---------------------👍 The Good:---------------------+  This is like brushing with a pillow! So they are not so soft that they don't do anything, they get in all the nooks and crannies with all those seemingly extra bristles.+ They are black because they are charcoal infused bristles (they have charcoal in the fibers) which removes plaque bacteria.+ Can be used for anyone kids loves it as it looks small & cool, Good for our elders too as teeth become sensitive with the age and it doesn't hurt gums, even you can use it for your pets they will love it too as it is too soft.+ There is no limit to what they could be used for. I would also use these outside of brushing - they would be good for cleaning things like jewellery, keyboard and items that are fragile as well.+ Rubberized coating with dotted texture on them at your thumb and finger points provide excellent grip in the hand.+ Not so pricey you get 3 at cost of two along with the extra 30% discount on amazon. 'Sensitive teeth' results from damaged enamel coating our teeth have. It can be due to improper care, use of rough tooth whitening substances or even too rough brushing.Once a tooth has been infected, the 'brushing' part might not be much effective. You'll NEED to visit a dentist asap.But mild sensitiveness can be treated by proper dental care, using sensitive toothpastes, soft toothbrushes and potassium nitrate gel (ONLY DO SO after consulting with your dentist !).Been using Sensodyne Soft toothbrush along with Colgate Total toothpaste for some years now and the results were satisfactory.Remember that just a brush or toothpaste cannot save you from toothache. It is a detailed & daily process, where we need to take proper care of our teeth.The item I bought was manufactured on May 2017 (bought on August 2017).MRP : 100 Rs (the same I've paid)

review_title: Nice, lightweight, but compared to competition ?
reviews: Prior to receiving this Panasonic Sonic Vibration Toothbrush I was primarily using one of these Philips Sonicare Essence Premium Rechargeable Sonic Toothbrush, which I got as a set of 2 (his and hers in our household). I must admit that I was perfectly fine with that Sonicare Toothbrush but I found myself intrigued at giving this Panasonic Toothbrush a thorough evaluation. What Ive found, in my own use of this Panasonic Toothbrush is that it does do, or at least seems to do, a good job of brushing my teeth and leaving my mouth feeling fresh but at the same time it doesnt seem to be significantly better than the Sonicare Toothbrush that I was previously using, which, by the way, costs significantly less than this Panasonic Toothbrush does (and also costs less, in most cases, to obtain accessories for).Pros:Nice, lightweight, comfortable to hold. (Lighter than the Sonicare, but given normal use, probably not that much difference for most users).Automatic timer/pause feature to indicate how long the brush has been running. (The Sonicare also includes an automatic cut-off timer, but doesnt pause at the 30 second mark like this Panasonic Toothbrush does).Offers a slight delay in warming up to full power which gives you a chance to get ready for the full power level. (Sonicare brushes, at least the ones I have used, do not offer that feature as once turned on, they immediately go to full power).Cons:Expensive when compared to competing products. (Typical Sonicare brushes can be found for far less.).Expensive to purchase accessories for. (Brush heads seemed to be more expensive with fewer third party options available, if any are available at all. With Sonicare brushes, third party heads can be found at most major big-box style retailers, as well as here at Amazon).I like this Panasonic EW-DL91-W Sonic Toothbrush, but Im not sure Id run out and spend the money to buy more of these unless/until the price comes down significantly. I would be very interested in hearing what dental hygienists and dentists think of this Panasonic Toothbrush. I have gotten compliments on the effectiveness of my brushing while using the Sonicare brushes, and expect Id get similar results when visiting the dentist on my next regularly scheduled appointment (coming up soon now actually).Bottom line: expensive, but does a good job. Someone that would like a very nice Sonic Vibration Toothbrush that is nice and lightweight might find this Toothbrush worth the premium pricing.

I have been using a Phillips Sonicare for about the last five years and had the opportunity to replace it with this Panasonic EW DL91. I keep this plugged in an outlet in my bathroom. I love the power of this mighty Tooth Brush! My teeth feel so clean after brushing! The Panasonic seems to have a lot more vibration than my old Phillips Sonicare. I like the design,in regards to, how the brush attaches to the base. There is no hollow base like there was with my old Sonicare where gook could build up. The Panasonic is lightweight and portable and has a linear drive motor. The linear motor operates at 28, 500 brush stokes per minute. I like the 2 vibration modes, one slower and the other faster. The brush timer pauses once every 30 seconds and twice every 2 minutes which indicates the recommended total brushing time. Brushes included triple brushing head that is designed for the surface of the teeth and between teeth and gums. 100% waterproof includes carrying case and illuminated display charger or brush head holder. Dimensions 6.5 inch height x 1 inch width x 1.1 inch depth, 4.4 ounce.  Panasonic warrants this for 2 years. Replacement brushes look like they run around $30.00 for a three pack. That is less than replacement brushes for the Sonicare. The only thing I wish they had included was a tooth brush head cover. I really dont like leaving my tooth brush head exposed. I am using the head cover off the Phillips Sonicare replacement brush, which fits nicely on the Panasonic as well. I hope this lasts a long time and the power stays consistant with use. I have struggled with gum disease for many years and I highly recommend purchasing this product or one like it. It really makes a big difference! With regular Dental visits and using this type of toothbrush, the routine has kept my gum disease under control. I could never go back to using a regular tooth brush! Well worth the investment!

I was pleasantly surprised with how much I like this panasonic sonic vibration toothbrush.  It is a lot different than other electronic toothbrushes.  The vibration feels a little funny at first, so it does take a bit to get used to.  But this toothbrush works very well and encourages proper brushing.  It has a timer than pauses the vibrations in 30 second intervals so you can divide your mouth into 4 sections and make sure that each section gets the appropriate amount of attention, and then it pauses longer at 2 min to indicate a proper full brushing time.  My teeth arent squeaky clean after using this, but it does a very good job.  It also comes with attachments for gums and something that is useful for getting hard to reach in between places and stuck food.  Also included are a carrying case and the base stand.  All in all, I really like this toothbrush and think you will too IF the idea of sonic vibrations feeling a bit odd is okay with you.

My dentist recommends an electronic toothbrush over a manual one.  Over the years I have sampled a slew of electronic toothbrushes.  After trying this Panasonic Sonic Vibrations brush, I have to include its a good (but pricey) option.-The sonic clean feels amazing and lasts for hours.  The sonic clean is the cleanest I have ever been able to get my teeth from a home toothbrush. This brush is so powerful that my lips are a little numb after using.-The brush is very lightweight (comparable to a manual toothbrush).-Briefly stops and restarts every 30 seconds so you can easily clock your brushing.  Honestly when brushing with this brush, I didnt even notice that feature until I read about it.  But it is there and does work.-Comes with two additional heads standard; a flossing type brush and a rubbery head for a more aggressive clean.  These brushes will probably be used infrequently, but are nice to have for occasional longer brushing sessions.-It does not hold a charge well.  I get 2-3 uses per charge, so Ive ended up leaving the brush constantly charging.-Ladies Toothbrush?  The brush is pink.  I would have preferred a more gender neutral color stock.  The brush head is also really small.  Oral B s heads are small too, so that they can cup the tooth, but they are also round unlike the more standard head Panasonic has.  But due to the color and size, I wouldnt purchase this as a gift for my father.Oral B 3000 is still my favorite toothbrush, and the one I will be continuing to purchase going forward.  You simply cant beat the bang for the buck.  Compared to the Panasonic the Oral B: holds a charge longer, offers more speeds and settings, has a better base including covers for replacement heads, is less expensive, comes with a travel case, the replacement heads are easier to find, and it offers a whitening setting.  I do feel my teeth are a little more clean after using the Panasonic, but there is only a slight edge and in my opinion not enough to mitigate the higher price and loss of additional features.
